{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01K5FVUdgqQDaXr8pYDy5UTG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. This is a design-mode task (Complexity: atomic) for the `metrics` component.\n\nLet me design this:\n\n**Package:** `metrics` (package name), located at `internal/metrics`\n\n**Files:**\n1. `store.go` — `EventStore` struct with `Add` and `List` methods; thread-safe via `sync.Mutex`\n2. `handlers.go` — `PostEvent` and `GetEvents` handler functions\n3. `routes.go` — `NewRouter` function returning `http.Handler`\n\n\n4. `store_test.go` and `handlers_test.go` — unit tests for the store and HTTP handlers using `httptest`\n\n**Data model:** An `Event` struct with ID, Type, UserID, and a flexible payload map for arbitrary data.\n\n**EventStore:** A thread-safe store that manages events with methods to add new events (auto-generating UUIDs) and retrieve the full list.\n\n**UUID generation:** I'm deciding between using the standard library with `crypto/rand` for UUID-v4 generation or pulling in `github.com/google/uuid` as a dependency — the latter is more standard in production Go services, so I'll go with that.\n\n**Handlers:** Building HTTP endpoints to accept event submissions and list stored events, starting with validation of the incoming request payload.\n\n**Routes:** Setting up a simple router using the standard library's ServeMux to wire the handlers to their respective paths.\n\n**Testing:** Since there's no go.mod file yet, I'll need to account for that when setting up the test command. For now, I'll specify the test command assuming the module root is the output directory parent and the test runs on the `internal/metrics` package.\n\nActually, looking at the output dir: `/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/metrics`\n\nThe module root will likely be at `.../output/` with